\int \frac{\pi}{2} \cos\left(\frac {\pi x}2\right) \,dx
u = \dfrac {\pi} 2 x \implies du = \dfrac{\pi}{2}\,dx \iff \,dx = \dfrac{2}{\pi}\,du
\int \frac \pi 2 \cdot \cos (u) \cdot \left( \dfrac 2\pi\,du\right) = \int \cos u\, du
